## Example 2 — Midsegment Length = Average of Bases

A trapezoid has bases of length 14 cm and 22 cm. Find the length of the midsegment.

### Step 1: Apply the Midsegment Theorem

$$\text{Midsegment} = \frac{\text{Base}_1 + \text{Base}_2}{2} = \frac{14 + 22}{2} = \frac{36}{2} = 18 \text{ cm}$$

### Step 2: Verify the Reasoning

The midsegment connects the midpoints of the two legs. Each half of the midsegment averages the corresponding half-bases, so the total midsegment averages the two full bases.

✅ Answer: The midsegment is **18 cm**.

